============================================================
PART 3: GAUSS SUM CONNECTION
============================================================
For circulant tournaments, S_hat(k) = sum_{s in S} omega^{ks}
The imaginary part D(k;sigma) = sum_{i=1}^m sigma_i * sin(2*pi*k*i/p)
h_hat[{i,j}] involves the product D(k;i)*D(k;j) summed over k

  p=7:
    D^T D matrix (sum_k sin(2pi*k*a/p)*sin(2pi*k*b/p)):
         1.750  -0.000   0.000
        -0.000   1.750  -0.000
         0.000  -0.000   1.750

    Comparison h_hat[{i,j}] vs D^T D [i,j]:

    Comparison h_hat[{i,j}] vs sum_k Q_k*D_k(i)*D_k(j):
    (1,2): h_hat=      3.50, Q*D^TD=  3.5000, ratio=      1.00
    (1,3): h_hat=     -3.50, Q*D^TD=  1.7500, ratio=     -2.00
    (2,3): h_hat=     -3.50, Q*D^TD=  1.7500, ratio=     -2.00

