============================================================
PART 4: INTERVAL EVALUATION OF WALSH SUMS
============================================================
At Interval (sigma = all +1):
  chi_S(sigma_Int) = 1 for all S
  So f_d(Int) = sum_{|S|=d} h_hat[S]
  = sum of ALL degree-d Walsh coefficients

  p=7:
    deg 0: f_d(Int) =        178.5  (+:1, -:0, 0:0)
    deg 2: f_d(Int) =         -3.5  (+:1, -:2, 0:0)
    sum f_d = 175.0 vs H(Int) = 175

  p=11:
    deg 0: f_d(Int) =      93101.2  (+:1, -:0, 0:0)
    deg 2: f_d(Int) =        280.5  (+:6, -:4, 0:0)
    deg 4: f_d(Int) =       -354.8  (+:1, -:4, 0:0)
    sum f_d = 93027.0 vs H(Int) = 93027

  p=13:
    deg 0: f_d(Int) =    3695839.9  (+:1, -:0, 0:0)
    deg 2: f_d(Int) =      -1556.8  (+:5, -:7, 0:3)
    deg 4: f_d(Int) =      16891.9  (+:8, -:7, 0:0)
    sum f_d = 3711175.0 vs H(Int) = 3711175

